com.google.gcloud.bigquery

Class Job

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.gcloud.bigquery.Job

  • public final class Job
extends Object
    A Google BigQuery Job.

    Objects of this class are immutable. To get a Job object with the most recent information use reload(com.google.gcloud.bigquery.BigQuery.JobOption...).

        Parameters:

        options - job options

      • isDone

        public boolean isDone()
        Checks if this job has completed its execution, either failing or succeeding. If the job does not exist this method returns false. To correctly wait for job's completion check that the job exists first, using exists(): 
         if (job.exists()) {
   while(!job.isDone()) {
     Thread.sleep(1000L);
   }
 }
        Returns:
        true if this job is in JobStatus.State.DONE state, false if the state is not JobStatus.State.DONE or the job does not exist
        Throws:
        BigQueryException - upon failure

      • reload

        public Job reload(BigQuery.JobOption... options)
        Fetches current job's latest information. Returns null if the job does not exist.
        Parameters:
        options - job options
        Returns:
        a Job object with latest information or null if not found
        Throws:
        BigQueryException - upon failure
